{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Previous research has addressed the trade-off between realism and controllability in safetycritical scenario generation by integrating various constraints.",
    "These include inference-time sampling techniques [43], retrieval-augmented generation [44], low-rank fine-tuning approaches [45], and language-conditioned generation methods [46].",
    "However, these efforts primarily focus on behavioral scenario generation without incorporating visual information.",
    "With advancements in Neural Radiance Fields (NeRF) and 3D Gaussian Splatting (3DGS), recent studies such as DriveArena [5] and MagicDrive [47] have begun developing E2E simulators for closed-loop evaluation.",
    "Similarly, RAD [19] employs a 3DGS-based simulator for RL fine-tuning."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "These include inference-time sampling techniques [43], retrieval-augmented generation [44], low-rank fine-tuning approaches [45], and language-conditioned generation methods [46].",
